Description: Elongated, conical shaped clay object, that was probably a gaming piece. It was fired and is mainly covered in black from fire. The clay contains inclusions of mica. The top of the object shows an irregularly shaped hole of about 0.4 x 0.6 cm with a depth of 0.5 cm. The base is flat with a slight curving inwards.
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 173)
